				<td colspan="2"><span>Well today i went on my first big adventure.
<br />
I told them that my wind wasnt up to par (65 i think) and that i would try and mez, but that it wasnt always going to cut it. It was like any group, cept these guys knew i could do more then mana song, which made me work, i was snaring DSin, lulling (of course hehe), healing, manaing, and buffing str. Oh and i was on mezzing when it needed to get done.
<br />
So we are having fun, but they are working me, plus im distracted like half the time by phone, and parents (not good). We had a bad pull, mezz cept skipin notes. Couple guys got killed. Then i got ragged to death, that i wasnt up to par, even though i had explained that. We failed the mission by like 5 mobs, then the guy who was looting went LD (magically) and we just end up leaving. We are suppost to meet up and divid what we got, i had won a blue dimond that i was suppost to get. But they group disbands and im left with the one page of something worth a nice 1 gold piece that i had looted by mistake. 
<br />
All in all it was a super adventure.
<br />
Just wondering does this crap happen often? Also for you bards out there, are we responsible for everything? I mean its been what ... 9 months since i was in a group that needed all that. It was fun but the rag'in i really hate..</span></td>
