				<td colspan="2"><span>Yeah, if you aren't extremely experienced with LDoN and exactly what ALL you can do with your bard at the same time (haste, slow, melee, pull, CC, DS, snare, etc.) it is advisable to make sure you have a group consisting of a cleric (maybe a Chealing druid), slower/haster (Chanter/Shammy/BST), tank (War, Pal, SK), CC (Chanter/you), and tons of DPS (rogue or nukers), to insure success with limited frazzled bard syndrome.  I have been Everything for my group twice (as detailed in my LDoN thread, hehe) and OMG it was hectic.  Fun to know you CAN be everything, but it's a ton easier to have the classes represented that can allow you to do as little of that extensive list as possible.  No I'm not lazy, no more than the tanks that move and attack or the cleric that heals and sits... far less for that matter, and they are essential classes, hehe.  
<br />

<br />
GL and enjoy the fast pace lifestyle of LDoN.
<br />

<br />
Sinfonian</span></td>
