				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Fisrt LDoN experiance...<a name="13337"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 16 03 11:32 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I've been in a couple of groups where I was expected to take the place of a shammy and chanter so they could bring in more DPS.  I've found that in a pickup group this is a really bad way to go since you don't know the capabilities of the other people in the group and mistakes will happen.  In these cases I usually say, &quot;get a chanter or shammy or you'll lose the bard.&quot;  It seems kind of selfish, but I'm here to have an enjoyable experience not spend an entire evening stressed out and finger twisted.
<br />

<br />
For you other bards new to LDoN a few other things you should work on are pick lock, sense and disarm traps.  Since I'm typically the puller I'll be mashing my sense traps key as there are some traps that are brutally annoying and I haven't found one yet that I couldn't sense or disarm.  Pick lock I've not had to use yet, but I've been told there's a few things that you need to have it for.
<br />

<br />
Happy adventuring and remember... it's the bards that rock<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /></span></td>
