				<td colspan="2"><span>I'm a 58 bard and i must say that Ldon is awsome for our class.  Im getting close to the 150 mark on wins with only 4 loss's.  When looking to put a group together i look for Healer, dps, dps, dps, dps.  I have no problems pulling, mezing, and doing the regular bard song twists during fights, infact i asume that this is what is expected of us.
<br />

<br />
Like most i to have had a few bad experiences.  One involved a very immature player that just happened to be our MT.  For some reason just as we started our adventure he disbanded and left us with me to tank in a caster group.  I dont know about most bards but my weapon set up is not ment to hold agro.
<br />

<br />
Playing in Ldon has many rewards.  I like most people do love those tells that let you know that your doing an awsome job, and that they had no idea bards could be so powerful in groups.  The stray tells i get from people who i have grouped with in Ldon asking to join there group also brightens my day.  
<br />

<br />
I have met and became friends with many people because of Ldon.  Yes we all have had bad times in some Ldon pickup groups, but by far i think the rewards far outweigh the negative aspects.</span></td>
