				<td colspan="2"><span>I tried my first LDoN (assassination) as a bard a few days ago with extremely satisfying results.  Group consisted of me, cleric, SK, shammy, rogue, and a druid.  Going into the dungeon, I insisted on being the puller, and they all decided that we could try it and see how it went.  I was a little nervous thinking that lull would fail and we would wipe, but it went off without a hitch... no failed lulls at all.
<br />

<br />
Long story short, we beat that dungeon into submission in less than 45 minutes.  I was pulling as fast as I could with lull / Fufil's to aggro and the mobs were just getting eaten alive as soon as they got near the SK.  He would snag the mob, I would stick around to twist a little haste, DS, mana, or Chant, then I would move ahead and grab the next mob at about 25% health.  It was great, and the group LOVED it.  Almost zero downtime for medding and the pulls were constant and consistent and predictable.  I got tells afterward that made me smile for the rest of the day <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-11.gif" border="0" alt="Cool" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
Felt good to be a Bard <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-10.gif" border="0" alt="Blushing" hspace="2" />They are definitely the crowd pleasers hehe.</span></td>
