		</table></td><td class="PanelBody" valign="Top"><table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3" border="0" width="100%">
			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Fisrt LDoN experiance...<a name="13377"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 18 03 9:47 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Well after a few LDoN Adventures I have come up with the following conclusions:
<br />

<br />
1 - Most pick up groups suck if not managed by one person
<br />

<br />
2 - Pally's are best LDoN pullers, Bards a close second. Why? They can take a better beating. 
<br />

<br />
3 - Guildmates and friends are the best groups as everyone is comfortable with what the other is doing.
<br />

<br />
4 - We can do it all. We are the proverbial hole fillers. I prefer to be the overhasting, dex buffing, slow/snaring type with a bit of resist, oos or even regen to smooth everything out. If we have a haster (chanter/shammy) I let them do their job, but I still sing VoV with my Battle-Drummer Main Gauche for the AC, STR and AGI boost. The Dex boost with Katta's is too d*mn sweet and is always requested by my guildmates. Then I use Largo's Absonant Binding for the AC and AGI debuffs as well as snare any potential runners. If I have no lag issues and can keep a 4-song twist going, I throw in Battlecry of Vah Shir or, if needed Cantata of Replenishment, Elemental Chorus (if against caster) and Occlusion of Sound. 
<br />

<br />
example: Had an adventure with all Fate's Presence folks. We select Hard for difficulty and do a collect mission. No problem in finishing it, even with stingy MoBs not giving us the collection. After that mission, we decide to do another. Two people had to jet, so we fill the gaps with a couple LFG sorts. We select Normal Rescue. Why? Because we were unsure of our new adventure mates' abilities and knew that the four of us could complete a normal mission. 
<br />

<br />
LDoN is all about the success. Leave your Ego at the door. If I am invited into a group, which takes a whopping second from my switching LFG on, and I find some blabbering numbskull talking about how great they are and that we should do a difficult mission &quot;'cause they're uber&quot;. Then I simply state &quot;Baby's crying gotta go&quot; and get out before they can even get the adventure going. You may have to go afk and sit for 15 minutes but it's well worth it.
<br />

<br />
If you're not comfortable with a grou you can always find another, is my humble and honest opinion</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
